.TH CISFUN 1 "21 September 2023" "1.0" "CisFun Shell Manual"
.SH NAME
.B CisFun
- A Simple UNIX Command Line Interpreter.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B CisFun
[OPTIONS] [SCRIPT]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B CisFun
shell is a lightweight UNIX command line interpreter. It reads and executes commands from the standard input or a specified script file.
.PP
CisFun is designed for simplicity and ease of use, making it suitable for basic scripting and interactive use.
.SH OPTIONS
The following options are supported by
.B CisFun:
.PP
.TP
.B -h, --help
Display a help message and exit.
.TP
.B -v, --version
Display the version information.
.SH USAGE
To start the
.B CisFun
shell interactively, simply run:
.PP
.B
$ CisFun
.PP
To execute commands from a script file, use:
.PP
.B
$ CisFun scriptfile
.PP
To exit the shell, type:
.PP
.B
$ exit
.SH BUILT-INS
The following built-in commands are supported by the
.B CisFun
shell:
.PP
.TP
.B env
Print the current environment variables.
.TP
.B setenv VARIABLE VALUE
Initialize a new environment variable or modify an existing one.
.TP
.B unsetenv VARIABLE
Remove an environment variable.
.SH RETURN VALUE
The
.B CisFun
shell exits with a status of 0 on successful execution of commands. Non-zero status may be returned in case of errors.
.SH SEE ALSO
.I sh(1)
.SH BUGS
There are currently no known bugs in the
.B CisFun
shell. If you encounter any issues, please report them to the author.
.SH AUTHOR
CisFun was created by Michael Adesina and Olanrewaju Awoyemi.
.PP
For updates and support, visit the official CisFun website.

